BVD-CAIRO-QUA-001	Unused Events	Events defined in a contract but never emitted represent dead code and missing observability. Events are critical for off-chain monitoring, user interfaces, and indexers to track contract activity. Defined but unused events indicate incomplete implementation, potential bugs where events should be emitted, or unnecessary code bloat that increases deployment costs and complexity.	code-quality	medium	\N	\N	A04:2021	{"description": "Remove unused event definitions or implement proper event emission where appropriate. Ensure all significant state changes emit corresponding events for transparency and off-chain tracking. Follow the pattern of emitting events after state updates but before external calls.", "code_example": "// PROBLEMATIC: Event defined but never emitted\\n#[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]\\nstruct OwnershipTransferred {\\n    previous_owner: ContractAddress,\\n    new_owner: ContractAddress,\\n}\\n\\n#[external(v0)]\\nfn transfer_ownership(ref self: ContractState, new_owner: ContractAddress) {\\n    let previous = self.owner.read();\\n    self.owner.write(new_owner);\\n    // Event never emitted!\\n}\\n\\n// CORRECT: Emit the event\\n#[external(v0)]\\nfn transfer_ownership(ref self: ContractState, new_owner: ContractAddress) {\\n    let previous = self.owner.read();\\n    self.owner.write(new_owner);\\n    self.emit(OwnershipTransferred { previous_owner: previous, new_owner });\\n}"}	[]	[{"url": "https://github.com/crytic/caracal", "title": "Caracal - Unused Events"}, {"url": "https://book.cairo-lang.org/ch99-02-02-contract-events.html", "title": "Cairo Events"}]	{}	0	{}	\N	{}	2025-11-08 17:33:26.003313+00	2025-11-29 01:51:10.107442+00	t
